body:
The official RPG modpack for the Corned Beef Corner. If you don't know what that is, not sure how you arrived here.

There's a few mods that have been modified from their original files. Mostly for either consistency with other mods in the pack, or because parts of the mod just didn't work and required me to fix it myself. And some are just simply from a diferent website.
Those mods are as follows: 

Traveler's Backpack - [https://modrinth.com/mod/travelersbackpack](https://modrinth.com/mod/travelersbackpack) 
//changed the GUI to have icons consistent with Inventory Management.

Towers of the Wild: Reworked - [https://modrinth.com/datapack/towers-of-the-wild-reworked](https://modrinth.com/datapack/towers-of-the-wild-reworked) 
//fixed a line of code that caused the regular variant of towers to not generate. This issue is known by the mod author as they've posted this fix on github, but they've yet to update the mod.

Axolotl Bucket Fix - [https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/axolotl-bucket-fix](https://www.curseforge.com/minecraft/mc-mods/axolotl-bucket-fix) 
//I used this one instead of any of the others on Modrinth because it's compatible with the More Axolotl Variants Mod which I very much enjoy.

Vanilla Tweaks - [https://vanillatweaks.net](https://vanillatweaks.net) 
//obviously there isn't a Modrinth page for this because the resource and data packs are incredibly modular. But I've also edited the variated villagers' textures to work properly with Fresh Animations.
